## Pre-Delivery Security Checklist

Before shipping any new endpoint or server action:

- [ ] Session checked at the top (or documented why it's public)
- [ ] Input validated with Zod schema
- [ ] Rate limiting applied (if public endpoint)
- [ ] User input escaped before regex/queries
- [ ] No IDOR — user can only access their own data (or resource is intentionally public)
- [ ] File uploads validate magic bytes, not just MIME type
- [ ] Secret comparisons use `crypto.timingSafeEqual`
- [ ] Credit operations use transactions + ledger entries
- [ ] Response only includes necessary fields (`.select()`)
- [ ] Error messages don't leak internal details
- [ ] New authenticated routes added to `src/proxy.ts` matcher
- [ ] `src/proxy.ts` exists (Next.js 16+ convention) with `export default` — no `src/middleware.ts` present
- [ ] Login/auth changes maintain brute-force protection
- [ ] Security headers verified with `curl -sI` after deploy

---

## Production Deployment Checklist

These items are NOT needed in local dev but MUST be addressed before going live:

### 🌐 HTTPS & Transport
- [ ] Enable HTTPS on all environments (Vercel/Railway/etc handle this automatically)
- [ ] Add `Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload` header once HTTPS is confirmed
- [ ] Redirect all HTTP traffic to HTTPS (301)
- [ ] Set `NEXTAUTH_URL` to the production `https://` domain
- [ ] Set `secure: true` on session cookies (NextAuth does this automatically when URL is https)

### 🔑 Secrets & Environment
- [ ] Generate fresh production secrets — NEVER reuse dev secrets:
  - `NEXTAUTH_SECRET` — minimum 32 random characters (`openssl rand -base64 32`)
  - `CRON_SECRET` — separate from dev
  - `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY` — production IAM user with minimal permissions
- [ ] Rotate all secrets that were ever committed or shared in dev
- [ ] Verify `.env` is in `.gitignore` and NOT in the deployed image
- [ ] Set secrets via the platform's secret management (not env files in production)

### 🛡️ WAF & DDoS Protection
- [ ] Enable Cloudflare, AWS WAF, or Vercel's built-in protection
- [ ] Set up bot detection / challenge pages for suspicious traffic
- [ ] Configure geographic restrictions if the platform targets specific regions
- [ ] Enable automatic SSL certificate renewal

### 📊 Monitoring & Alerting
- [ ] Set up error tracking (Sentry, Bugsnag, or Vercel's built-in)
- [ ] Monitor for 5xx spikes, latency anomalies, and auth failure rates
- [ ] Alert on: >10 failed logins per minute (credential stuffing), >50 4xx per minute (scanning)
- [ ] Log all admin actions (market resolution, user modifications) to an immutable audit log
- [ ] Set up uptime monitoring with a health check endpoint

### 🗄️ Database Security
- [ ] MongoDB Atlas: enable IP allowlisting (only your app servers)
- [ ] Use a dedicated database user with minimal permissions (no `dbAdmin` role)
- [ ] Enable MongoDB audit logging for production
- [ ] Enable encryption at rest and in transit (Atlas does this by default)
- [ ] Set up automated backups with point-in-time recovery
- [ ] Test restore procedure at least once before launch

### 🔒 Content Security Policy (Production)
- [ ] Add a strict CSP header once all third-party scripts are identified:
  ```
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: *.s3.amazonaws.com; connect-src 'self' *.googleapis.com; font-src 'self' fonts.gstatic.com;
  ```
- [ ] Test CSP in report-only mode first (`Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only`)
- [ ] Set up CSP violation reporting endpoint to catch issues

### 🔄 Rate Limiting (Production-Grade)
- [ ] Replace in-memory rate limiter with Redis-backed solution (Upstash, Redis Cloud)
- [ ] In-memory maps reset on deploy/restart — Redis persists across instances
- [ ] Add rate limiting per API key if you ever expose a public API
- [ ] Consider separate rate limit tiers: anonymous (stricter) vs authenticated (relaxed)

### 📧 Account Security
- [ ] Add email verification on registration (send confirmation link before activating account)
- [ ] Implement password reset flow with time-limited tokens
- [ ] Add optional 2FA (TOTP) for admin accounts at minimum
- [ ] Send email notification when password is changed or new device logs in
- [ ] Implement session invalidation ("sign out all devices")

### 🔍 Penetration Testing
- [ ] Run OWASP ZAP or Burp Suite scan before launch
- [ ] Test all auth flows manually: registration, login, password reset, session expiry
- [ ] Test IDOR: change IDs in URLs while logged in as different users
- [ ] Test file upload with malformed files, oversized files, path traversal filenames
- [ ] Verify rate limits actually fire (send burst traffic with `ab` or `wrk`)

### 📋 Compliance & Legal
- [ ] Add privacy policy page (what data is collected, how it's stored, how to delete)
- [ ] Add terms of service (virtual credits have no monetary value, no gambling disclaimer)
- [ ] Implement data export (GDPR: user can download their data)
- [ ] Implement account deletion (GDPR: right to be forgotten)
- [ ] Cookie consent banner if serving EU users (analytics cookies, auth cookies are exempt)
